Alabama Gov. Robert Bentley orders flags on state buildings at half staff for Rev. Shuttlesworth
Sherrel Stewart -- The Birmingham News By on October 05, 2011 at 5:14 PM, updated
MONTGOMERY (AP) -- Alabama Gov. Robert Bentley has ordered the flags on state government building lowered to half-staff in memory of civil rights leader the Rev. Fred Shuttlesworth.
Shuttlesworth died Wednesday in a Birmingham hospital.     The governor called him "a true pioneer for civil rights" and "an Alabama treasure."      Bentley said the flags will remain lowered until sunset on the day of Shuttlesworth's interment.